%% RHOAI Operator (rhods-operator) - Data Flow Diagram
%% Generated by: Claude Opus 4.6

sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User Browser
    participant Route as OpenShift Route / LB<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant Envoy as data-science-gateway<br/>(Envoy Proxy)<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Filter as EnvoyFilter<br/>(data-science-authn-filter)
    participant AuthProxy as kube-auth-proxy<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS mTLS
    participant OAuth as OpenShift OAuth Server<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant Backend as Backend Service<br/>(via HTTPRoute)

    Note over User,Backend: Flow 1: User Authentication via Gateway (OAuth Mode)

    User->>Route: GET /dashboard<br/>HTTPS/443, No Auth
    Route->>Envoy: Forward request<br/>TLS terminate
    Envoy->>Filter: Intercept for auth
    Filter->>AuthProxy: External auth check<br/>HTTPS/8443, mTLS (Istio)
    AuthProxy->>OAuth: Validate token<br/>HTTPS/443, OAuthClient creds
    OAuth-->>AuthProxy: Token valid / redirect to login
    AuthProxy-->>Filter: Auth result (allow/deny)
    Filter-->>Envoy: Continue or 403
    Envoy->>Backend: Forward with auth headers<br/>HTTP/HTTPS

    Backend-->>Envoy: Response
    Envoy-->>Route: Response
    Route-->>User: HTML/JSON Response

    Note over User,Backend: Flow 2: Component Deployment via DSC

    participant Admin as Cluster Admin
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant Webhook as Operator Webhook<br/>9443/TCP HTTPS
    participant DSCCtrl as DSC Controller
    participant CompCtrl as Component Controllers

    Admin->>K8sAPI: Create DataScienceCluster CR<br/>HTTPS/6443, Bearer Token
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: Validate CR<br/>HTTPS/9443, API server client cert
    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Admission allowed
    K8sAPI-->>Admin: CR created

    K8sAPI->>DSCCtrl: Watch event: DSC created
    DSCCtrl->>K8sAPI: Create Component CRs<br/>(Dashboard, Kserve, Ray, etc.)<br/>HTTPS/6443, SA token

    K8sAPI->>CompCtrl: Watch event: Component CR created
    CompCtrl->>K8sAPI: Deploy kustomize/helm manifests<br/>HTTPS/6443, SA token

    Note over User,Backend: Flow 3: Monitoring Stack Metrics Collection

    participant Prom as MonitoringStack<br/>(Prometheus)
    participant Targets as Component Targets<br/>(ServiceMonitor)
    participant Thanos as ThanosQuerier<br/>9090/TCP HTTP
    participant OTel as OpenTelemetry Collector
    participant Tempo as Tempo<br/>4317/TCP gRPC
    participant Perses as Perses Dashboards

    Prom->>Targets: Scrape metrics<br/>HTTP/HTTPS, SA token
    Thanos->>Prom: Query metrics<br/>HTTP/9090
    OTel->>Tempo: Send traces (OTLP)<br/>gRPC/4317, optional TLS
    Perses->>Prom: Query datasource<br/>HTTP/9090
